<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <!--
    Better Traders Guild - Paramedic Mech Medic Duty

    BTG_MechMedic: medbay-anchored medical triage for the Paramedic mech. Tending is
    confined to the mech's MedicalBay (resolved by rect membership in MedicRoomBounds,
    never a radius - so an arbitrarily large or multi-rect medbay works exactly); rescue
    reaches out across the rest of the settlement structure to bring casualties in.

    Priority order:
    1. Tend - patch the worst wounded same-faction defender IN the medbay (worst bleed,
       then lowest health), in a bed or on the floor, using the highest-potency medicine
       in the room. endAfterTendedOnce keeps re-triaging one casualty at a time, and the
       medbay is cleared before the medic walks out to fetch anyone else.
    2. Rescue - carry a downed defender lying OUTSIDE the medbay but inside the structure
       footprint to an unreserved medical bed in the medbay (worst-bleed first). No-op
       when no in-medbay bed is free; the casualty waits where they are.
    3. Idle - dormant self-charge (SelfShutdown, forceSleep off so the LayDown re-check
       wakes it for the next casualty within ~211 ticks).

    Used by: LordJob_MechMedic, assigned via RoomMechLordHelper to the Paramedic mech
    (RoomPart Mech_Paramedic, behavior=Medic).
  -->

  <DutyDef>
    <defName>BTG_MechMedic</defName>
    <thinkNode Class="ThinkNode_Priority">
      <subNodes>
        <!-- 1. Stabilize and Tend defenders in the medbay, worst-first (bed or floor), best medicine first. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.Mechs.JobGiver_BTGMechMedicTend" />
        <!-- 2. Rescue downed defenders from outside the medbay, prioritizing free hospital-beds. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.Mechs.JobGiver_BTGMechMedicRescue" />
        <!-- 3. Idle: dormant self-charge; re-checks ~every 211 ticks to wake for casualties. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.Mechs.JobGiver_BTGMechMedicStandby" />
      </subNodes>
    </thinkNode>
  </DutyDef>

</Defs>
